    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "So the workmen wrought,.... The masons, carpenters, blacksmiths, and brasiers: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the work was perfected by them; the business of repairs was completely finished: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they set the house of God in his state; as it was at first: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and strengthened it; so that it seemed as firm and stable as when first built. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and strengthened it; so that it seemed as firm and stable as when first built. ",
            "children": []
